headline: On the Night of the True Enemy, I tried to find the ring nebula!

attachment.altText: Saturn with a second saturn overlapping on top of it
Jupiter shining brightly with four dots: the galilean moons!
Two stars which are split into smudges, and one faint blue line which the caption claims is the ring nebula... but probably isn't the ring nebula

markdown.content: For the record, past me was wrong. That's not the ring nebula. There aren't two bright stars aligned like that near the ring nebula. But that's the prettiest Jupiter I've ever taken!
(Why is there a double saturn? [I know why now!](https://cohost.org/hillexed/post/2597705-the-true-enemy-revea))
